Ridge View Raptors
4 hrs ·

To help limit the spread of COVID-19 and to allow our student athletes to participate in sports, we are limiting the number of spectators at our events this week.

Tuesday, September 15, Ridge View is hosting River Valley Community School District and Oabcig Community School District in Schaller for Varsity Volleyball. Each of our Varsity players will be given 5 tickets. Opposing teams will be given a limited number of tickets. This ticket entitles the bearer to attend the game, but he/she will still need to pay/use activity pass before being admitted. If you do not have a ticket, you can not attend the game. Face masks are required at all home volleyball games.

The volleyball game is available to watch via live stream at nfhsnetwork.com. Choose Ridge View and subscribe. You will get all the home volleyball and football games for $11/month. Cancel subscription anytime. It's super easy and convenient and you help support your Raptors with every subscription.

Thank you for your continued support and understanding during this unique time in our lives.

post_text:
SPECIAL SCHOOL ELECTION
TUESDAY, SEPTEMBER 8

Polls open 7:00 a.m. to 8:00 p.m.

The OABCIG District will be holding a special election to re-vote on the district’s Revenue Purpose Statement. The Revenue Purpose Statement specifies the use of the penny sales, services and use tax for schools (sales, services and use tax funds from secure an advanced vision for education fund for school infrastructure also known as SAVE.) Due to recent legislation that extended the sunset date on the SAVE fund, school districts must vote on extending the expiration date on the district’s current statement.

post_text: The 7th and 8th graders finished their first project, water colored color wheels. The students built upon their knowledge of primary, secondary, and tertiary colors and also practiced using watercolor which can be tricky to work with. The students had to mix several colors to achieve the colors throughout the color wheel. They also wrapped up their week by playing an art game where students had to utilize the skills they learned earlier by mixing 2 colors to achieve the same color they saw in front of them.

NOTICE OF VACANCY:
The OABCIG Community School District has openings for Cook Positions. Odebolt Building-approximate hours 8:30 to 1:30. High School in Ida Grove-approximate 3-4 hours per day. Positions are during school year. Benefits include IPERS, paid sick and personal leave. Must have the physical capability to do the lifting required in the preparation, serving & cleaning up of meals as directed by the Food Service Director, have a basic knowledge of food preparation & enjoy working with children & adults. Support Staff Application is available on the school website or at the district office in Ida Grove. Please return letter of interest & completed application to: Attn: Mary Renze, Food Services Director-OABCIG Schools, 900 John Montgomery Drive, Ida Grove, Iowa, 51445. Positions will remain open until filled. OABCIG Community School Districts is an Equal Opportunity provider & employer.

post_text:
UPDATED INFORMATION
Deluxe Driving Academy
Driver Education
OABCIG High School
Classroom and Driving Information

2020 Summer Session

Parents, there will be 3 driving teachers for this session. We will schedule driving dates and times the first day of class at 8:00 am. Students will be driving in groups of 2. Mr. Walsh will drive with 16 students. Mr. Smeltzer will drive with 14 and Mr. Ryan 20. Please talk to your child about pairing up with another student and have your child bring their schedules with them so we can schedule with minimal conflicts.

There will be a change of location for the class due to construction changes at the high school. Class will now be held in the old gym at elementary in Ida Grove.

1. Masks are required in the car,
2. Masks recommended in classroom.
3. Phones only allowed during breaks.
4. Using phones during class will be grounds for dismissal.
5. You can miss 2 classes but both have to be made up at another site.
6. If you have symptoms of the virus please do not come to class.
7. Please use social distancing when in the classroom.

post_text:
OABCIG Community Schools will serve as a distribution site for the "Farmers to Families Food Box" program being sponsored by the USDA, in cooperation with Iowa farmers and food distributors.

Boxes of meat (15 pounds) will be available FREE to those wanting to pick them up. It will be first come, first serve and quantities are limited.

Pick up sites are as follows:
Ida Grove - High School loading dock (West side of building)
Odebolt - Elementary/Middle School main entrance
Battle Creek – at the in-town bus stop

Distribution of boxes will begin at 4:30pm on Thursday, June 4th and continue until boxes are gone or 5:30pm (whichever comes first).

post_text:
2020-2021 Cheerleading tryouts will be on Saturday, June 6th at the High School gym. Wear shorts, t-shirt, and tennis shoes!

Practice will be from 9:00-12:00. You must come to practice in order to try-out at 12:00. You will learn basic arm motions and kicks, a group cheer, and 2 individual cheers. You will need to know the words to the school song (found on this school webpage: http://www.oabcig.org/cheerleading). If you are trying out for football or basketball you will be asked about stunting skills.

Tryouts will start at noon. We will put you in groups of 3-4 to be judged.

post_text:
OABCIG Spanish students had the opportunity to take a Spanish proficiency test that tested them on their speaking, writing, listening, and reading skills in Spanish. The Iowa Seal of Biliteracy shows that students have at least reached an intermediate level in all aspects of 2 languages, in this case English and Spanish.

Five of our Senior students were able to score high enough on their exams to receive the Iowa Seal of Biliteracy. Those 5 Seniors were Jennifer Godbersen, Sarah Petersen, Evan Veltri, Lea Williams, and Josie Wulf. If you see any of these Seniors make sure to congratulate them on their awesome achievement!

We apologize for the delay in providing information for commencement. We have been working with the Public Health Department to create a ceremony on May 17. Due to the uncertainty pertaining to large gatherings we have decided to host a Virtual Commencement on May 17, followed by an in-person ceremony on June 28.

Thank you for your patience. Please contact the high school office 364-3371 with questions or concerns.

post_text:
Our communities continue to show our school such a generous spirit!! Our school meal program has received more sought after supplies & monetary donations!! We appreciate Chris Reed Construction for donating lunch sacks & styrofoam trays, the Knights of Columbus for donating t-shirt bags (plastic grocery type), the Ida Grove Lutheran Church Group donated take-out trays, & Stan & Denise Chisholm donated $100 to be used towards supplies necessary for serving so many children in our communities!!

Our school feels blessed to have wonderful businesses & community members supporting our efforts!!🙌🏻

**In order to improve social distancing that is beneficial for the safety of our meal distribution staff, a new routine is being implemented. Please allow 1 person to exit your vehicle & walk up to the table to collect your meals. It’s appreciated that so many have brought a bag or laundry basket in order to pick up & place the meals for transport.😉

post_text:
With so many activities canceled for our children - let's do something fun and creative for the kids!

Hang an egg in your house window for kids to hunt for while they are on a walk or riding in the car around their communities!

🐰Color a paper egg!

🐣Hang a plastic egg!

🥕Use Easter decorations!

Walk or drive around your neighborhood and count how many eggs you can find!

Feel free to let us know how many eggs you have found or attach a picture in the comments of your family creating their own special eggs! Let's add some color to our communities!

We've attached some egg coloring pages for you to use if you want!
